Lasagna

1 lb ground meat
3 c tomato sauce
12 lasagna noodles
1 lb ricotta cheese
1 lb mozzerella, shredded
1/2 c. parmesan cheese

Brown ground meat.  Add tomato sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.

Cook lasagna noodles halfway.

Lightly cover bottom of a 13" pan with a little sauce.
Add 4 noodles, half of the ricotta , a third of the sauce, and half of
the mozzerella. Repeat.  Place remaining noodles on top then cover with
remaining sauce.  Sprinkle parmesan cheese on top.

Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.  Let stand for 10 minutes.
